---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Block Tom"
	description="An English-first personal site for essays, app product pages, and app-specific privacy policies."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-05-12')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
	lang="en"
>
	<p>
		Block Tom is my English-first personal site. It keeps longer essays, product notes, and the public pages
		my apps need, especially app-specific privacy policies.
	</p>

	<h2>What Lives Here</h2>
	<p>
		The writing section is for ideas, reading notes, and opinion pieces that should stay findable beyond a
		social media timeline. The products section is for apps and tools: product introductions, platform notes,
		download links, support information, and privacy policy links.
	</p>

	<h2>Language</h2>
	<p>
		English is the primary version of this site. Chinese versions are kept under the <code>/zh/</code> path so
		the same material remains available in both languages without making the main site harder to read or index.
	</p>

	<h2>Products And Privacy</h2>
	<p>
		Every app can have its own product page and its own privacy policy page. That keeps privacy statements
		separate by product instead of forcing unrelated apps into one generic document.
	</p>
</Layout>
